Different ways to inject react
CDN (content delivery network { link })
open browser and write react cdn
crossorigin - The crossorigin attribute
sets the mode of the request to an
HTTP CORS Request. Web pages often
make requests to load resources on
other servers. Here is where CORS
comes in. A cross-origin request is a
request for a resource (e.g. style sheets,
iframes, images, fonts, or scripts) from
another domain.
The React CDN contain two links
react.js :- Its the core of the react
reactDom.js :- And the dom is used to perform operation on dom and
it help to do some changes in dom like creating a child and other operation
the dom link was added because react does not works only in browser
which also work for mobile and other like react native
Creating a react element using REACT CDN
<body>
<script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.development.js"></script>
<script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.development.js"></script>
<script>
const heading = React.createElement('h1', {}, "Kain");
const root = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('id'));
root.render(heading)
</script>
</body>
